The chairman Ungogo local government council of Kano State, Engr. Abdullahi Garba Ramat, has inaugurated and flagged off three projects valued at over N1 billion. The three projects are renovation and upgrade of Abdullahi bin Mas’ud Primary School at Bachirawa, perimeter fencing of Bachirwa Abattoir, the on-going 5km dual carriage road with drainages from both side and culverts at strategic locations from kwanar Ungogo to Ungogo town and inauguration of Juma’at/Eid prayer mosque at Karo ward. Engr. Ramat said the projects were embarked upon based on need assessment conducted in the area.